[thinking] **Evaluating object initialization**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering how to handle an object of a non-exported type that needs to be treated as an Object. I wonder if the class object needs to be initialized before the fake class. It looks like the DirectByteBufferPool object is lazy, meaning it doesn't get created until it's needed. I think testing can help configure the system, and then we can focus on releasing it later on.
[thinking] 
